P(X = x\ |\ Y = y)
E(X \ |\ Y=y)
\sum_x P(X = x\ |\ Y = y)
P(X = x) = \sum_y P(X=x\ |\ Y=y) P(Y=y)
E(X) = \sum_x x P(X = x) = \sum_x x \left(\sum_y P(X = x\ |\ Y=y) P(Y=y)\right)
{} = \sum_y \left( \sum_x x P(X=x\ |\ Y= y) \right) P(Y=y) = \sum_y E(X\ |\ Y =y) P(Y=y).
